title: ID-H-3
treatment_protocol_ch1: Hyperglycemic condition was induced by treatment of 24 hours after HUVEC reach 80% confluency  with 33.3 mmol/L D-glucose
growth_protocol_ch1: HUVEC were maintained in endothelial cell medium supplemented with 5% fetal bovine serum (FBS) and antibiotics in humidified atmosphere with 5% CO2 at 37C
extract_protocol_ch1: RNA was harvested using miRNeasy mini kit (Qiagen). 1 ug of total RNA was used for the construction of sequencing libraries.
extract_protocol_ch1.1: Library was performed according to the manufacter’s instructions.
data_processing: Basecalls were performed using bcl2fastq v2.17.1.14 for Novaseq output.
data_processing.1: RNA-seq reads were trimmed from 5' or 3' end until the final base had a quality score > 20, using Trimmomatic v0.30, discarding reads left with < 18 bp
data_processing.2: RNA-seq reads were mapped to a reference genome (Homo sapiens GRCh38.104) using Bowtie version 2.1.0.
data_processing.3: The microRNA differential analysis was performed using the Bioconductor package DESeq2 (V1.6.3)
data_processing.5: Supplementary files format and content: tab-delimited text files include TPM values for each Sample
